      <section class="content-section">
        <div class="container">
          <p>Blocked drains cause serious problems—backing up sewage, flooding, and expensive emergency repairs. The good news is that most blockages are preventable through regular maintenance and smart drainage practices. Here's how to keep your drains flowing freely.</p>

          <h2>The Kitchen Sink: Your Biggest Drain Threat</h2>
          <p>Kitchen drains accumulate the most problematic material. Grease congeals as it cools, catching food particles and building blockages. Cooking oil and fat should never go down drains—dispose of them in the bin. Coffee grounds, tea leaves, and food scraps shouldn't enter drains either. Use sink strainers to catch debris, and regularly clean strainers rather than allowing them to fill up and force water over blockages.</p>

          <h2>Don't Flush These Items</h2>
          <p>Toilets only accept human waste and toilet paper. Anything else causes blockages. Never flush:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Wet wipes (including "flushable" wipes—they don't break down like toilet paper)</li>
            <li>Cotton buds and cosmetic wipes</li>
            <li>Sanitary products</li>
            <li>Dental floss</li>
            <li>Hair</li>
            <li>Nappies or incontinence products</li>
            <li>Food waste</li>
            <li>Grease or oil</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Hair Management</h2>
          <p>Hair accumulates in bathroom drains, creating blockages over time. Install drain covers in showers and baths to catch hair before it enters pipes. Clean accumulated hair from drain covers regularly rather than allowing it to build up and force its way down.</p>

          <h2>Regular Drain Maintenance</h2>
          <p>Don't wait for blockages to appear. Regular maintenance prevents problems. Monthly, pour boiling water down drains (carefully) to clear minor buildups. For periodical deeper cleaning, use drain-cleaning products or have professional drain cleaning performed annually. This is particularly important for older properties with clay or cast iron drainage pipes susceptible to root damage.</p>

          <h2>Tree Root Prevention</h2>
          <p>Mature trees seeking moisture are attracted to drainage pipes. Tree roots infiltrate cracks, growing inside pipes and causing serious blockages. If you have large trees near drainage infrastructure, consider professional CCTV surveys every few years to identify root damage early. In some cases, professional treatment prevents expensive excavation later.</p>

          <h2>Autumn Leaf Management</h2>
          <p>Autumn leaves block gutter systems, and overflow causes drainage problems. Regular gutter cleaning prevents leaves from entering drainage systems. This is particularly important in properties surrounded by mature trees.</p>

          <h2>Washing Machine Drainage</h2>
          <p>Washing machine discharge sometimes accumulates lint and sediment, causing blockages. Ensure your washing machine drainage doesn't have sharp bends that trap debris. Professional cleaning of washing machine discharge pipes during annual maintenance prevents buildup.</p>

          <h2>Outside Drains and Gullies</h2>
          <p>External gullies often collect debris and sediment. Regular clearing prevents standing water and blockages. Check around your property for drain covers and gullies, and ensure they're clear of leaves, soil, and debris.</p>

          <h2>Watch for Warning Signs</h2>
          <p>Slow drainage, gurgling sounds, or foul smells indicate developing problems. Address these early—they're easier and cheaper to fix before complete blockage occurs. A professional drain inspection identifies problems before emergencies develop.</p>

          <h2>Professional Help</h2>
          <p>Annual professional drain cleaning is valuable insurance. Our CCTV drain surveys identify problems visually, and professional jetting clears buildup that home maintenance can't address. This is particularly valuable in older Bristol properties with period drainage systems.</p>

          <h2>When Blockages Happen</h2>
          <p>Despite prevention efforts, blockages sometimes occur. Don't use caustic drain cleaners that damage pipes—call us instead. Our high-pressure jetting and professional equipment clear blockages safely without damaging your drainage system.</p>
